1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,720
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,720 --> 00:00:04,720
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:07,960
My name is Catherine and today we have an intermediate level lesson for you.
我是Catherine，今天我们为大家准备了一节中级课程。

4
00:00:07,960 --> 00:00:09,560
It's kind of about cars, right?
这跟车有点关系，对吧？

5
00:00:09,560 --> 00:00:10,560
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:15,600
So today we are taking our car to the mechanic and we're just going to check things and make
所以今天我们要把车开到修车厂，

7
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:16,920
sure that our car is okay.
检查一下确保车况良好。

8
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:17,920
All right.
好的。

9
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:22,680
So we're going to learn a lot of really great words that have to do with cars and what happens
我们会学到很多跟汽车相关的实用词汇，

10
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:24,000
when cars break down.
以及汽车出故障时的情况。

11
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
So let's listen to our dialogue.
那我们来听一下对话吧。

12
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:35,520
Welcome to Al's Garage.
欢迎来到Al's修车厂。

13
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:37,280
What seems to be the problem?
有什么问题吗？

14
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:38,480
No problem at all.
完全没问题。

15
00:00:38,480 --> 00:00:44,240
I am taking a long road trip and I want to make sure my car is in good mechanical condition.
我要开长途旅行，想确保车况良好。

16
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:45,840
Very wise decision.
非常明智的决定。

17
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:48,800
When was the last time you had a tune-up?
你上次做保养是什么时候？

18
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:50,160
Not that long ago.
没多久之前。

19
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:52,480
I think it was four months ago.
我想是四个月前。

20
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:56,440
We usually recommend that you bring your car in every 5,000 kilometers.
我们通常建议每5000公里来检查一次。

21
00:00:56,440 --> 00:00:57,440
Why?
为什么？

22
00:00:57,440 --> 00:01:02,720
I mean, what exactly do you do to a car that you need to check it so often?
我是说，到底要对车做什么检查，需要这么频繁？

23
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:05,940
First of all, we change the motor oil and oil filter.
首先，我们会更换机油和机油滤清器。

24
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:10,440
If you don't do this, it can cause your engine to wear faster and that means you would probably
如果不这样做，会导致发动机磨损加快，

25
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:13,280
have to change the pistons and intake valves.
那就可能得换活塞和进气阀了。

26
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:14,840
I see.
我明白了。

27
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:15,960
What else?
还有什么？

28
00:01:15,960 --> 00:01:21,480
We also check your spark plugs, fuel filter, and other oil levels such as hydraulic fluid.
我们还会检查火花塞、燃油滤清器，以及其他油液，比如液压油。

29
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:25,320
We also check the clutch and brakes to determine when you will need new ones.
还会检查离合器和刹车，判断什么时候需要更换。

30
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:26,320
Okay.
好的。

31
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:30,600
Well, when you put it that way, it doesn't seem like a waste of time and money.
嗯，听你这么一说，这倒不像是浪费时间和钱了。

32
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:31,600
Trust me.
相信我。

33
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:36,320
Regular tune-ups will keep your car running smoothly and avoid breakdowns.
定期保养能让你的车运行顺畅，避免抛锚。

34
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:42,240
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

35
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:47,920
So a very simple dialogue with the mechanic explaining to the client about why you need
这段对话很简单，修车师傅向客户解释了

36
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,720
to take care of your car.
为什么需要保养车。

37
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:52,560
So he mentioned a couple of very technical words in here.
他提到了几个很专业的词。

38
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:57,720
Let's take a look at those on Language Takeaway.
我们来看看“语言要点”部分。

39
00:01:57,720 --> 00:02:00,360
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

40
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:03,640
The first phrase we're looking at today is tune-up.
今天要学的第一个短语是tune-up。

41
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:09,040
So a tune-up is a thing, it's a noun, and it's something you do to check your car.
Tune-up是个名词，指的是对车进行检查。

42
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:10,040
Right.
对。

43
00:02:10,040 --> 00:02:13,520
So you take your car for a tune-up or you get a tune-up.
所以你可以说“把车送去保养”或“做一次保养”。

44
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:19,200
Now this is for your car and this basically means to check that your car is okay and replace
这是针对车的，基本上就是检查车况，

45
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:23,840
any very easy things around the car.
并更换一些简单的部件。

46
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:27,060
So you don't normally get a tune-up when your car is broken.
通常车坏了不会去做保养。

47
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:29,160
You get a tune-up when your car is okay.
车况好的时候才做保养。

48
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:30,360
That's right.
没错。

49
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:35,640
So the mechanic explained some of the things that you do when you get a tune-up.
修车师傅解释了保养时做的一些事情。

50
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:39,520
So for example, he said that they change the motor oil.
比如，他说他们会更换机油。

51
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:44,360
Okay, so like it sounds, motor oil is oil for your motor.
对，顾名思义，机油就是发动机用的油。

52
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,360
That's right.
没错。

53
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:51,400
And there are other kinds of oil as well and oil is oftentimes put into the car and then
还有其他种类的油，油经常被加进车里，

54
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,400
sometimes it falls out.
有时也会漏出来。

55
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:55,680
And so what's that thing that catches the oil when it comes down?
那油漏下来时接住它的东西叫什么？

56
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,680
It's called an oil pan.
叫油底壳。

57
00:02:57,680 --> 00:03:00,760
So yes, as you said, there are different types of oils.
是的，就像你说的，有不同类型的油。

58
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:03,480
Cooking oil is obviously for cooking, for eating.
食用油当然是用来做饭、吃的。

59
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:06,800
But motor oil is not for eating, it's for your motor.
但机油不是用来吃的，是给发动机用的。

60
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:09,540
But we also have to change the oil filter.
我们还得更换机油滤清器。

61
00:03:09,540 --> 00:03:13,280
Now this is an important part that often gets mentioned at tune-ups.
这是保养时经常提到的重要部件。

62
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:14,280
That's right.
没错。

63
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:18,600
So the word filter here, you have the verb to filter.
Filter这个词，有动词形式“过滤”。

64
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:22,340
In this case, we also have a noun, it's called a filter.
这里它是名词，叫滤清器。

65
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:28,000
So what this device does, it collects maybe dirt or rocks and dust or anything that you
这个装置的作用是收集灰尘、石子、污垢等

66
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:33,320
don't want to be in your engine and specifically maybe if the oil is a little bit dirty.
你不希望进入发动机的东西，特别是如果机油有点脏的话。

67
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:39,720
Right, so an oil filter makes sure that the oil in your motor is not going to harm your
对，机油滤清器确保发动机里的机油不会损害发动机。

68
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:41,320
motor.


69
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:45,040
And we also have a couple of interesting things like the fuel filter.
我们还有一些有趣的东西，比如燃油滤清器。

70
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:47,640
Now how is this different from the oil filter?
它和机油滤清器有什么不同？

71
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:49,280
It's pretty much the same thing.
基本一样。

72
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:55,760
The only difference is that this filter specifically cleans the gasoline in your car.
唯一的区别是这个滤清器专门清洁车里的汽油。

73
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:58,000
Okay, similar object.
好的，类似的东西。

74
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,560
After that, we have something very different.
之后，我们有一个很不同的东西。

75
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:01,460
These are spark plugs.
这是火花塞。

76
00:04:01,460 --> 00:04:02,460
That's right.
没错。

77
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:06,480
These are small little devices that, as the name says, create a spark.
这些小装置，顾名思义，会产生火花。

78
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,720
This is how your engine goes.
发动机就是这样工作的。

79
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:08,720
This is how your car moves.
车就是这样动的。

80
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:12,160
You have a spark and then everything starts running.
有了火花，一切就开始运转了。

81
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:14,200
Spark plugs are actually quite important, right?
火花塞其实挺重要的，对吧？

82
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,200
That's right.
没错。

83
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:21,320
So a spark is a very quick flash of light that comes out.
火花就是一瞬间闪出来的光。

84
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,320
That's right.
对。

85
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:23,320
It's not a long light.
不是持续的光。

86
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,320
It's just a spark.
只是一闪而过的火花。

87
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:29,720
So maybe when I strike a match or I use a lighter, there's a spark and that's what starts
所以，比如我划火柴或用打火机时，会有火花，那就是点燃

88
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:30,720
the fire.
火焰的东西。

89
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,720
That's right.
没错。

90
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:32,720
That's exactly right.
完全正确。

91
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,520
So a spark plug.
所以是火花塞。

92
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:40,440
And now we also check the oil levels of our car and that's a very important thing as well.
现在我们还会检查汽车的机油量，这也是很重要的事。

93
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:41,440
Yeah, that's right.
是的，没错。

94
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:45,760
So the oil level is something that you test with a long stick and you put it into the
机油量是用一根长棍来检测的，把它插进

95
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:50,180
engine, the oil container, and make sure that there is enough oil because if there's not
发动机的机油箱里，确保机油足够，因为如果机油

96
00:04:50,180 --> 00:04:53,560
enough oil, you can have very serious car trouble.
不够，可能会引发严重的汽车故障。

97
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,560
That's right.
没错。

98
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:58,680
So a lot of technical or mechanical things that we're taking a look at.
所以我们看了很多技术或机械方面的东西。

99
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:11,160
Why don't we go back, let's review all these words and we'll be back in a bit.
我们不如回顾一下，复习所有这些词，一会儿再回来。

100
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,720
Welcome to Al's Garage.
欢迎来到阿尔的修车厂。

101
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,480
What seems to be the problem?
有什么问题吗？

102
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,680
No problem at all.
完全没问题。

103
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:21,440
I am taking a long road trip and I want to make sure my car is in good mechanical condition.
我要进行一次长途旅行，想确保车况良好。

104
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:23,040
Very wise decision.
非常明智的决定。

105
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:26,000
When was the last time you had a tune-up?
你上次做保养是什么时候？

106
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,360
Not that long ago.
没多久之前。

107
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,680
I think it was four months ago.
我想是四个月前。

108
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:33,760
We usually recommend that you bring your car in every 5,000 kilometers.
我们通常建议每5000公里把车送来检查一次。

109
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:34,760
Why?
为什么？

110
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:39,880
I mean, what exactly do you do to a car that you need to check it so often?
我是说，到底要对车做什么检查，需要这么频繁？

111
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:43,100
First of all, we change the motor oil and oil filter.
首先，我们会更换机油和机油滤清器。

112
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:47,600
If you don't do this, it can cause your engine to wear faster and that means you would probably
如果不这样做，会导致发动机磨损更快，那可能就得

113
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:50,440
have to change the pistons and intake valves.
更换活塞和进气阀了。

114
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:52,000
I see.
我明白了。

115
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,120
What else?
还有呢？

116
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:58,640
We also check your spark plugs, fuel filter, and other oil levels such as hydraulic fluid.
我们还会检查火花塞、燃油滤清器，以及其他油液，比如液压油。

117
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:02,680
We also check the clutch and brakes to determine when you will need new ones.
我们还会检查离合器和刹车，判断什么时候需要更换新的。

118
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,680
Okay.
好的。

119
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:07,800
Well, when you put it that way, it doesn't seem like a waste of time and money.
嗯，听你这么一说，这倒不像是浪费时间和钱了。

120
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,800
Trust me.
相信我。

121
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:13,840
Regular tune-ups will keep your car running smoothly and avoid breakdowns.
定期保养能让你的车运行顺畅，避免抛锚。

122
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:19,440
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

123
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:22,240
So now we've prepared three key phrases for you.
现在我们为你准备了三个关键短语。

124
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:26,600
Let's take a look at those now on Fluency Builder.
让我们在流利度练习中看看这些。

125
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,360
Fluency Builder.
流利度练习。

126
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:31,760
This first phrase is something that you often hear in the service industry.
第一个短语在服务行业经常听到。

127
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:37,200
So anytime you're going to a shop or maybe in this case, the mechanic, the mechanic will
所以，无论你去商店，还是像这里去修车厂，修车工会

128
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,980
say to you, what seems to be the problem?
对你说：“有什么问题吗？”

129
00:06:39,980 --> 00:06:40,980
That's right.
没错。

130
00:06:40,980 --> 00:06:44,080
So this is a question and we're saying, what is wrong with your car?
这是一个问句，意思是“你的车出了什么问题？”

131
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:47,760
Or maybe if you go to the doctor, the doctor will say, what seems to be the problem?
或者，如果你去看医生，医生也会说：“有什么问题吗？”

132
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:49,360
What seems to be the problem?
有什么问题吗？

133
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:51,360
So this means what's wrong with you?
所以这意思是“你哪里不舒服？”

134
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:53,160
Where do you have a problem?
“你哪里有问题？”

135
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:54,640
This is a very, very common phrase.
这是一个非常非常常见的短语。

136
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:55,640
So remember this one.
记住这个。

137
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:57,040
It just means what's going on?
它只是表示“发生什么事了？”

138
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:58,040
Why are you here?
“你为什么来这里？”

139
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,400
What can I help you with?
“我能帮你什么？”

140
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,640
It's very polite though, right?
不过它很礼貌，对吧？

141
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,280
It's better than saying what's wrong with you.
比直接说“你怎么了”要好。

142
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:03,280
No, yeah.
不，是的。

143
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:04,320
You wouldn't want to say what's wrong with you.
你不会想说“你怎么了”。

144
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:05,320
That's very rude.
那很粗鲁。

145
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:08,960
So what seems to be the problem is a much more polite way of saying things.
所以“有什么问题吗”是一种更礼貌的表达方式。

146
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:09,960
Very good.
非常好。

147
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:15,680
And well, the mechanic, after explaining everything, he said that, you know, doing all these things,
而且，修车工在解释完所有事情后说，做这些事，

148
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:19,320
changing the filters will keep the car running smoothly.
更换滤清器能让车运行顺畅。

149
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,320
Okay.
好的。

150
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:23,360
So we're not talking about running like a marathon here.
我们这里说的不是像跑马拉松那样跑。

151
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:26,200
We're talking about using your car.
我们说的是使用汽车。

152
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:30,240
And so when we turn a car on, we don't say that the car is operating.
当我们启动汽车时，我们不说车在“运行”。

153
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:32,720
Really, we say it's running.
实际上，我们说它在“运转”。

154
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:38,400
So that means that it's in use, that I've turned the key and the motor is running.
所以意思是它在使用中，我转动钥匙，发动机在运转。

155
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:42,360
But if it's running well, we say it's running smoothly.
但如果它运转良好，我们就说它“运行顺畅”。

156
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:44,280
So it's not having any problems.
所以就是没有任何问题。

157
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:45,280
Yeah.
是的。

158
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:49,520
So if you turn your car on and you hear your engine, it sounds very normal, no problems.
所以如果你启动汽车，听到发动机声音很正常，没问题。

159
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:51,240
It's running smoothly.
它运行顺畅。

160
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:55,040
If it's going, it's not running smoothly.
如果它有问题，就不是运行顺畅了。

